    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: October 3, 2025</p>

    <div class="highlight">
        <strong>Privacy First:</strong> Content Analytics Studio is designed with privacy at its core. All data processing happens locally on your device. We do not collect, store, or transmit your personal information or TikTok data to external servers.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Content Analytics Studio ("we," "our," or "the Application"), operated by Disenorg, handles information when you use our marketing analytics tool. We are committed to protecting your privacy and maintaining the confidentiality of your data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. Information We DO NOT Collect</h2>
        <p>Because the Application operates entirely on your local device, we do not collect:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Personal identification information (name, email, address)</li>
            <li>TikTok account credentials or passwords</li>
            <li>Your TikTok content or video data</li>
            <li>Analytics or performance metrics from your account</li>
            <li>Search history or usage patterns</li>
            <li>Device information or IP addresses</li>
            <li>Cookies or tracking data</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. How the Application Works</h2>
        <p>Content Analytics Studio operates as follows:</p>
        
        <h3>Local Processing</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>All AI models run locally on your device using Ollama</li>
            <li>No data is sent to cloud servers for processing</li>
            <li>All analysis and reports are generated on your computer</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>TikTok API Integration</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>When you authenticate with TikTok, the connection is direct between your device and TikTok's servers</li>
            <li>We only facilitate this connection; we do not intercept or store authentication data</li>
            <li>Your TikTok data remains under TikTok's privacy policies</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Data Storage</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>All files and reports are saved locally on your device</li>
            <li>You have complete control over your data</li>
            <li>You can delete all data at any time by removing the application folder</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. TikTok Data Usage</h2>
        <p>When you use TikTok's API through our Application:</p>
        
        <table>
            <tr>
                <th>Data Type</th>
                <th>Usage</th>
                <th>Storage</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>OAuth Tokens</td>
                <td>Authenticate API requests</td>
                <td>Local device only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Public Trends</td>
                <td>Analyze hashtags and content</td>
                <td>Local cache (temporary)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Your Video Metrics</td>
                <td>Generate performance reports</td>
                <td>Local files only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Account Information</td>
                <td>Display in dashboard</td>
                <td>Memory only (not saved)</td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <p>All TikTok data is subject to TikTok's Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>The Application may interact with the following third-party services:</p>
        
        <h3>TikTok API</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Used for accessing your TikTok data (with your permission)</li>
            <li>Governed by TikTok's Privacy Policy</li>
            <li>Direct connection from your device to TikTok</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Web Scraping (Public Data Only)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Used for analyzing publicly available trends and hashtags</li>
            <li>Does not access private or user-specific data</li>
            <li>Complies with robots.txt and terms of service</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement security measures to protect your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Local-Only Processing:</strong> No data leaves your device</li>
            <li><strong>No Cloud Storage:</strong> No servers to be compromised</li>
            <li><strong>Optional Encryption:</strong> Sensitive folders can be encrypted</li>
            <li><strong>Secure API Connections:</strong> All API calls use HTTPS</li>
            <li><strong>No Logging:</strong> We don't log or track your activities</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Your Rights and Control</h2>
        <p>You have complete control over your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> All your data is in plain files on your device</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Delete the application folder to remove all data</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Export your data at any time</li>
            <li><strong>No Account:</strong> No registration or account required</li>
            <li><strong>Revoke Access:</strong> Disconnect TikTok API access anytime through TikTok settings</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. GDPR Compliance</h2>
        <p>For users in the European Union, we comply with GDPR requirements:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> We process only necessary data locally</li>
            <li><strong>Purpose Limitation:</strong> Data used only for stated analytics purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Storage Limitation:</strong> You control data retention</li>
            <li><strong>Integrity:</strong> Data processed securely on your device</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Delete all data instantly by removing files</li>
            <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> All data in standard formats (JSON, CSV, MD)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>The Application is not intended for users under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect information from children. If you are under 18, please do not use this Application.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>10. Changes to Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected with an updated "Last Updated" date. Continued use of the Application after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>Since all processing occurs locally on your device, there are no international data transfers. When you use TikTok's API, data transfers are governed by TikTok's policies.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>12. Analytics and Tracking</h2>
        <p>We do not use:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Google Analytics or similar services</li>
            <li>Advertising networks</li>
            <li>Social media pixels</li>
            <li>Cookies or tracking technologies</li>
            <li>Usage monitoring or telemetry</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>13. Open Source Transparency</h2>
        <p>The Application is built using open-source technologies. You can verify our privacy claims by reviewing the source code and confirming that:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>No network calls are made except to TikTok API (when you authorize)</li>
            <li>All processing happens locally</li>
            <li>No data collection mechanisms exist</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>14. Contact Information</h2>
        <div class="contact">
            <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how your data is handled, please contact:</p>
            <p><strong>Company:</strong> Disenorg</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> marcos.valverde.mail@gmail.com</p>
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Madrid, Spain</p>
            <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We aim to respond within 48 hours</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>15. Data Protection Officer</h2>
        <p>For GDPR-related inquiries or to exercise your rights under GDPR, you may contact our data protection representative at the email address above.</p>
    </div>

